{"id":13982,"date":"2023-07-07T15:05:45","date_gmt":"2023-07-07T15:05:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/?p=13982"},"modified":"2023-07-07T15:05:48","modified_gmt":"2023-07-07T15:05:48","slug":"how-does-kht-get-water-to-villages","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/how-does-kht-get-water-to-villages\/","title":{"rendered":"How Does KHT Get Water To Villages?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>KHT&#8217;s gravity fed water system relies on the natural flow of water downhill to ensure water can reach villages from sources. This means that KHT finds a suitable water source, and from there builds its system. A hugely important part of this system are the pipes. Due to the jungles and hills, pipes need to be transported to the source and buried or placed strategically to ensure water can freely flow using gravity and without any obstructions. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Depending on how far the source it, we need enough pipes to reach the village and this can sometimes be more than 3 miles away and in a hard to reach location. Most of the materials that are transported to the source are done by people and no vehicles can reach the source. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13990\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392664.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13990\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392664.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392664-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392664-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392664-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Pipes are delivered to the village and you can see how many are needed!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13989\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392684.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13989\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392684.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392684-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392684-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392684-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Sometimes reaching the village is very difficult and our team must cross rivers, mud roads and dangerous slopes.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13988\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392694.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13988\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392694.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392694-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392694-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392694-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Our team and the villagers carry the pipes to where they will need to be laid. <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13987\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392702.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13987\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392702.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392702-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392702-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392702-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Pipes are sometimes placed around trees and down hill to ensure the steady flow of water.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13985\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392714.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13985\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392714.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392714-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392714-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392714-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Our team and the villagers will dig where the pipes will need to be buried along the route.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"674\" height=\"1200\" data-id=\"13986\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392716.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13986\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392716.jpg 674w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392716-169x300.jpg 169w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392716-575x1024.jpg 575w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" \/><figcaption>It is important to ensure the pipes are buried well to prevent issues and obstructions. <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-id=\"13984\"  src=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392737.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-13984\" srcset=\"https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392737.jpg 1200w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392737-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392737-1024x575.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/karenhilltribes.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/07\/S__1392737-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" \/><figcaption>Sometimes it is not possible to bury pipes and we need to hang them over trees and over streams or rivers. <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Organising and laying the pipes is physically demanding and can be a difficult task. To get the process completed we are supported by at least 20 volunteers from the village. They participate in the construction of the system and they also help maintain it after we leave, ensuring ownership and sustainability. KHT also ensures there are extra pipes should any replacements be needed over time. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whilst these pipe look unassuming and like simple plastic tubing, they are vital in helping people end water poverty and improve their health. You can help us reach more villages and ensure Karen people have access to water by <a href=\"http:\/\/www.karenhilltribes.org.uk\/donate\">donating <\/a>to our WASH projects today! <\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>KHT&#8217;s gravity fed water system relies on the&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":13983,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[28],"tags":[],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v19.12 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/pl